## ⚠️ KTU Examiner's Valuation Warning / Pitfall Callout

> [!WARNING]
> **Common Mistakes That Cost Marks in KTU Exams:**
>
> 1. **Writing `super()` after other statements** — This is a **compilation error**. `super()` or `this()` **must** be the first statement. Many students lose 1–2 marks here.
>
> 2. **Confusing `super.field` with `super.field()`** — `super.field` accesses a variable; `super.field()` invokes a method. Mixing them is a frequent typo.
>
> 3. **Forgetting the `outer.new Inner()` syntax** — To instantiate a non-static inner class, you must write `outerObj.new Inner()`, not `new Outer.Inner()`. Students commonly write the wrong syntax.
>
> 4. **Assuming Anonymous Inner Classes can implement multiple interfaces** — They can extend **one class** OR implement **one interface**, but not both and not multiple interfaces.
>
> 5. **Calling `super()` inside a static context** — `super` cannot be used inside `static` methods or `static` blocks because `super` refers to an instance.
>
> 6. **Not knowing the `.class` file naming convention** — KTU asks this as a 1-mark sub-question. Remember: `$` separates outer and inner names.
>
> 7. **Writing static methods/fields in a member inner class** — Compilation error unless it's a `static final` constant.

