### Question B1 (Choice A). `[KTU University Exam — Model Paper 2024]`
**(a)** Explain the three access specifiers in C++ with a suitable example demonstrating the use of `protected` members in a multi-level inheritance scenario. **(7 marks)**

**(b)** A derived class in C++ cannot access `private` members of the base class directly. Justify this statement and show how `protected` solves the problem. Write a complete C++ program to demonstrate. **(7 marks)**

