#### Model Solution for B2(b) — C++ vs Java Access Specifier Comparison

**Comparison Table (3 marks):**

| Feature                                    | C++                                    | Java                                              |
|--------------------------------------------|----------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------|
| Number of access specifiers                | 3 (`private`, `protected`, `public`)   | 4 (adds package-private / default)                |
| `private` accessible in derived class?     | ❌ No                                   | ❌ No                                              |
| `protected` accessible in same package?    | N/A (no packages)                      | ✅ Yes (also for non-derived classes)              |
| Cross-package `protected` access           | N/A                                    | ✅ Only through inheritance (subclass-type ref)    |
| Friend mechanism                           | ✅ Yes                                  | ❌ No                                              |
| Default access for `class`                 | `private`                              | Package-private                                   |
| Default access for `struct` (C++)          | `public`                               | N/A                                               |

**Java Program Demonstrating `protected` with Cross-Package Inheritance (4 marks):**

