Validation Failed: Invalid marks: -10. Marks must be between 0 and 100.
Validation Failed: Invalid marks: 150. Marks must be between 0 and 100.
Marks validated successfully: 72
```

#### Model Solution (Part B — b):

```java
class RethrowLogger {
    // Layer 1: Low-level method detects and logs
    static void databaseQuery(String query) throws Exception {
        try {
            if (query == null || query.isEmpty()) {
                throw new IllegalArgumentException("Query string is empty or null.");
            }
            System.out.println("Executing query: " + query);
        } catch (IllegalArgumentException e) {
            System.out.println("[Layer 1 Logger] Error logged: " + e.getMessage());
            throw e;  // Rethrow for higher-level handling
        }
    }

    // Layer 2: Mid-level method wraps and rethrows
    static void executeTransaction(String query) throws Exception {
        try {
            databaseQuery(query);
        } catch (Exception e) {
            System.out.println("[Layer 2 Wrapper] Wrapping exception for propagation.");
            throw new Exception("Transaction failed due to: " + e.getMessage(), e);
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        try {
            executeTransaction("");  // Triggers exception chain
        } catch (Exception e) {
            System.out.println("[Centralized Handler] Final error: " + e.getMessage());
            System.out.println("[Centralized Handler] Root cause: " + e.getCause().getMessage());
        }
    }
}
```

**Expected Output:**
```
[Layer 1 Logger] Error logged: Query string is empty or null.
[Layer 2 Wrapper] Wrapping exception for propagation.
[Centralized Handler] Final error: Transaction failed due to: Query string is empty or null.
[Centralized Handler] Root cause: Query string is empty or null.
```

> [!WARNING]
> **KTU Examiner's Valuation Pitfall — Where Students Lose Marks:**
> 1. **Forgetting the `throws` clause for checked exceptions:** If you `throw new IOException()` inside a method, you must either wrap it in `try-catch` OR add `throws IOException` in the method signature. Missing this causes a compilation error and **zero marks** in coding questions.
> 2. **Confusing `throw new Exception()` with `throws new Exception()`:** Students often write `throws new Exception()` in method signatures — this is syntactically wrong. Method signatures use `throws Exception` (no `new` keyword).
> 3. **Writing code after `throw` in the same block:** Any code after `throw` inside the same block is unreachable. The compiler will reject this with "unreachable statement" error. Always place `throw` as the **last logical statement** before the block ends.
> 4. **Throwing the wrong type for the question:** When the question asks for `IllegalArgumentException`, writing `throw new ArithmeticException()` is incorrect. Read the question carefully for the **specific exception class** required.
> 5. **Not showing stack trace handling:** KTU examiners award marks for catching the exception, printing `e.getMessage()`, and demonstrating proper recovery. Simply writing `catch(Exception e) {}` (empty catch) loses 2-3 marks.

