The `java.io.File` class (legacy) and `java.nio.file.Path`/`Files` (modern) represent file/directory paths abstractly. It does **not** open, read, or write file content — it only manages metadata.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **`File` ≠ File Content.** A `File` object represents the *pathname*; to read/write actual content, you must use streams.

