## 2.3 Common Pitfalls in File Handling

| Pitfall | Consequence | Solution |
|---|---|---|
| Forgetting to close stream | Resource leak, file lock | Use try-with-resources |
| Using `FileWriter` for binary data | Data corruption | Use `FileOutputStream` |
| Platform-specific line separators (`\n` vs `\r\n`) | Cross-platform issues | Use `BufferedWriter.newLine()` |
| Hardcoding file path with `\` on Windows | Compile error (`\` is escape char) | Use `\\\\` or `File.separator` |
| Reading a file that doesn't exist | `FileNotFoundException` | Always check `file.exists()` first |
