## 3.2 Step-by-Step: Working with the `File` Class

```java
import java.io.File;
import java.io.IOException;
import java.util.Date;

public class FileDemo {
    public static void main(String[] args) throws IOException {

        // Step 1: Create a File object representing a path (does NOT create the file yet)
        File f = new File("test.txt");

        // Step 2: Check if file exists; if not, create it
        if (!f.exists()) {
            boolean created = f.createNewFile();
            System.out.println("File created: " + created);
        }

        // Step 3: Display file metadata
        System.out.println("Name         : " + f.getName());
        System.out.println("Path         : " + f.getPath());
        System.out.println("Absolute Path: " + f.getAbsolutePath());
        System.out.println("Readable     : " + f.canRead());
        System.out.println("Writable     : " + f.canWrite());
        System.out.println("Size (bytes) : " + f.length());
        System.out.println("Is directory : " + f.isDirectory());
        System.out.println("Is file      : " + f.isFile());
        System.out.println("Last modified: " + new Date(f.lastModified()));

        // Step 4: Directory operations
        File dir = new File("myDir/subDir");
        if (!dir.exists()) {
            boolean made = dir.mkdirs();   // Creates both myDir and subDir
            System.out.println("Directory created: " + made);
        }

        // Step 5: List directory contents
        String[] children = dir.list();
        if (children != null) {
            System.out.println("Contents of " + dir.getName() + ":");
            for (String child : children) {
                System.out.println("  " + child);
            }
        }

        // Step 6: Delete file
        boolean deleted = f.delete();
        System.out.println("File deleted: " + deleted);
    }
}
```

### Trace Table for the Above Program

| Step | `f.exists()` | `f.length()` | `f.isFile()` | Action |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Before creation | `false` | 0 | `false` | Calls `createNewFile()` |
| After creation | `true` | 0 | `true` | Displays metadata |
| After write (external) | `true` | > 0 | `true` | `length()` updated |
| After delete | `false` | 0 | `false` | File removed from disk |

