## 3.5 Analytical Decision Matrix: When to Use Which Constructor

| Input Data Source | Best Constructor | Why |
|---|---|---|
| String literal `"abc"` | `new String("abc")` or directly `String s = "abc"` | Compiler optimization (string pool) |
| `char[]` from a text field | `new String(char[])` | Direct mapping, fastest |
| Subset of characters | `new String(char[], off, count)` | Avoid manual array copy |
| `byte[]` from socket | `new String(byte[], Charset)` | Explicit, safe encoding |
| `byte[]` of known format (e.g., ASCII) | `new String(byte[])` | Uses default charset (faster but risky) |
| Need Unicode code points | `new String(int[], off, count)` | Handles supplementary characters |
| Freeze `StringBuffer` content | `new String(StringBuffer)` | Defensive copy, thread-safety |
| Freeze `StringBuilder` content | `new String(StringBuilder)` | Defensive copy |
