## Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember (Rapid Revision Checklist)

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Last-Minute Revision Bullets — Read 3 times before the exam.**

### File Handling
- [ ] `File` class = path management only; **no I/O**.
- [ ] Two hierarchies: **Byte Streams** (`InputStream`/`OutputStream`) and **Character Streams** (`Reader`/`Writer`).
- [ ] **Byte streams** = binary; **Character streams** = text.
- [ ] Java I/O uses the **Decorator Pattern** — wrap a node stream with a processing stream.
- [ ] Always use **try-with-resources** (Java 7+) to auto-close streams.
- [ ] `FileInputStream.read()` returns `int`; `-1` indicates **EOF**.
- [ ] `BufferedReader.readLine()` returns `String`; `null` indicates **EOF**.
- [ ] `FileWriter(path, true)` → **append** mode. Default = overwrite.
- [ ] `DataInputStream`/`DataOutputStream` for primitive types in binary.
- [ ] `ObjectInputStream`/`ObjectOutputStream` for object serialization.
- [ ] Use `BufferedWriter.newLine()` — **not** `"\n"` — for cross-platform newlines.
- [ ] Throws `FileNotFoundException` (checked) when file doesn't exist.
- [ ] Throws `IOException` for general I/O failures.

### String Constructors
- [ ] `String` is **immutable**; `StringBuffer`/`StringBuilder` are **mutable**.
- [ ] `String(StringBuffer)` and `String(StringBuilder)` perform **defensive copies** (snapshot at construction time).
- [ ] Subarray constructors: `String(char[], off, count)` and `String(byte[], off, len)`.
- [ ] Boundary: `0 ≤ offset < length` AND `0 ≤ count ≤ length - offset`.
- [ ] Violation → `StringIndexOutOfBoundsException`.
- [ ] Charset-aware constructors: prefer `Charset` over `String` charset-name (no checked exception).
- [ ] `String(int[] codePoints, off, count)` handles **supplementary Unicode** (BMP+ characters like emoji).
- [ ] `String(byte[] ascii, int hibyte, int off, int count)` is **DEPRECATED** — do not use.
- [ ] The 13 **publicly available** constructors are the ones to memorize for the exam.
- [ ] `String()` (empty) vs `String("")` (empty literal) — both have `length() == 0`.

> [!NOTE]
> **Exam Tip:** When asked to "write a Java program using file handling," always include:
> (i) `try-with-resources` for stream closure,
> (ii) `FileNotFoundException` catch block,
> (iii) Buffering for efficiency,
> (iv) `System.out.println` for output.
> Missing any of these costs easy marks.
