# 5. KTU 2024 Scheme Examination Question Bank & Topic Recap

## 5.1 Part A — Short Answer Questions (3 Marks Each)

### **Q1. [KTU University Exam — May 2024]**
**Differentiate between invoking the `start()` method and the `run()` method of a `Thread`. What happens if `run()` is called directly without `start()`?**

#### **Model Answer (3 marks):**
- **`start()` (2 marks):** Creates a **new call stack** and registers the thread with the thread scheduler. The scheduler eventually calls `run()` on the new stack. Each thread runs independently.
- **`run()` (1 mark):** If called **directly** (e.g., `t.run()`), it executes as a **normal method call in the current thread's stack**. **No new thread is created**, and no concurrent execution occurs.
- **Bonus mark:** Mention that calling `start()` twice on the same thread throws `IllegalThreadStateException`.

---

### **Q2. [KTU University Exam — Dec 2023]**
**List any three methods of the `Thread` class and state their purpose.**

#### **Model Answer (3 marks — 1 mark each):**
1. **`start()`** — Initiates the thread; causes the JVM to call `run()` on a new call stack.
2. **`sleep(long ms)`** — Pauses the currently executing thread for the specified milliseconds (does not release locks).
3. **`join()`** — The calling thread blocks until the target thread completes execution.
4. *Alternative:* `getPriority()` / `setPriority()` for thread priority management.

